      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEE HEZA SPORT NZ (9) worked from a similar draw to this when finding winning form here two back before chasing well for second last time. Goes well at this longer distance, winning three races along with a second in last year's Nullarbor. Can go close. OUR CRUNCH TIME NZ (1) is a progressive gelding who scored first up at this venue then led and stuck on when 2 metres from the winner in second at Pinjarra. Has won two of three attempts here and has the speed to take advantage of the inside draw. SOHO MOONRAKER (2) ended last campaign with a win at this venue and also also kicked off the new campaign on a winning note, scoring by close to 2m at Pinjarra. Draws to be prominent again. YOURE SO FINE NZ (12) may need luck from the back row but has won here twice this time in, one of them from this barrier. Respect.",
